1 to explain, and disconnected from Louisiana's long-term goals for student readiness; and
2 WHEREAS, today there is no uniform and standardized process for traditional public
3 school systems to determine and document when a student is nonenrolled due to
4 incarceration or unknown whereabouts; and
5 WHEREAS, when a student is determined to be nonenrolled due to incarceration or
6 unknown whereabouts, the student is counted as enrolled for purposes of state accountability
7 systems as of the date of determination, which negatively affects the school and school
8 district's performance; and
9 WHEREAS, since Louisiana has adopted a revised school accountability system that
10 raises expectations for students, simplifies how school performance is measured, and makes
11 it easier for families and the public to understand how schools are preparing students for life
12 after graduation, it is only fitting that the state Department of Education study
13 implementation and accountability implications of student nonenrollment determinations.
14 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
15 does hereby request the state Department of Education study implementation and
16 accountability implications of student nonenrollment determinations.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that this study shall include, at a minimum, the
18 following:
19 (1) Establishment of a uniform and standardized process for traditional public school
20 systems to determine and document when a student is nonenrolled due to incarceration or
21 unknown whereabouts.
22 (2) A process comprised of documented, reasonable, and good-faith efforts to locate
23 and verify the student's enrollment status, and to specify minimum documentation
24 requirements, timelines, and verification procedures to ensure consistency and accuracy
25 across school systems.
26 (3) Effects associated with counting a student determined to be nonenrolled for
27 purposes of state accountability systems as of the date of determination on schools and
28 school districts after a good-faith effort is made to locate and verify the student's enrollment
29 status.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the state Department of Education shall submit
